WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.368 align:middle line:90%
[THEME MUSIC]

00:00:05.368 --> 00:00:19.322 align:middle line:90%


00:00:19.322 --> 00:00:21.030 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE NOORY: Welcome
to Beyond Belief.

00:00:21.030 --> 00:00:23.810 align:middle line:10%
Daniel Sheehan is a
constitutional lawyer.

00:00:23.810 --> 00:00:26.130 align:middle line:84%
And he deals with
subject matters that

00:00:26.130 --> 00:00:28.540 align:middle line:90%
are way beyond most people.

00:00:28.540 --> 00:00:31.440 align:middle line:84%
But today on Beyond
Belief, it's a subject that

00:00:31.440 --> 00:00:33.900 align:middle line:90%
deals with all of us every day.

00:00:33.900 --> 00:00:35.290 align:middle line:90%
It's called climate change.

00:00:35.290 --> 00:00:37.060 align:middle line:84%
And Daniel, welcome
to the program.

00:00:37.060 --> 00:00:37.690 align:middle line:84%
>>DANIEL SHEEHAN:
Thank you, George.

00:00:37.690 --> 00:00:38.490 align:middle line:90%
Good to be here.

00:00:38.490 --> 00:00:40.890 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Tell me how you
got involved in this.

00:00:40.890 --> 00:00:43.960 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: I was engaged in
all kinds of different things.

00:00:43.960 --> 00:00:45.990 align:middle line:90%
But one of them was I was--

00:00:45.990 --> 00:00:49.320 align:middle line:84%
I've been for years working
with the Lakota people

00:00:49.320 --> 00:00:51.930 align:middle line:84%
up in North and
South Dakota, helping

00:00:51.930 --> 00:00:55.170 align:middle line:84%
them stop having all
their children taken away

00:00:55.170 --> 00:00:56.950 align:middle line:84%
and put into the white
foster care homes.

00:00:56.950 --> 00:00:57.750 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Geez.

00:00:57.750 --> 00:01:01.530 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: And then subjected
to massive drugs and chemicals,

00:01:01.530 --> 00:01:03.870 align:middle line:84%
basically testing out
chemicals on them.

00:01:03.870 --> 00:01:04.670 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: On them.

00:01:04.670 --> 00:01:05.470 align:middle line:90%
>>SHEEHAN: Yeah.

00:01:05.470 --> 00:01:07.640 align:middle line:84%
And because of that,
I've gotten to know

00:01:07.640 --> 00:01:09.930 align:middle line:84%
lots of the people that
are in the tribal councils

00:01:09.930 --> 00:01:11.460 align:middle line:90%
and governments up there.

00:01:11.460 --> 00:01:15.730 align:middle line:84%
And when the Dakota Access
Pipeline and also the XL,

00:01:15.730 --> 00:01:17.910 align:middle line:84%
the Keystone XL
pipeline, were planned

00:01:17.910 --> 00:01:21.410 align:middle line:84%
to be drilled right straight
through their territory,

00:01:21.410 --> 00:01:23.390 align:middle line:84%
the Standing Rock
Sioux reservation,

00:01:23.390 --> 00:01:25.680 align:middle line:84%
which is just part of
the great Sioux Nation

00:01:25.680 --> 00:01:27.880 align:middle line:84%
up there, the great
Sioux reservation.

00:01:27.880 --> 00:01:31.290 align:middle line:84%
They started gathering
and demonstrating

00:01:31.290 --> 00:01:33.210 align:middle line:90%
against that being done.

00:01:33.210 --> 00:01:36.990 align:middle line:84%
And when the security
forces, the private security

00:01:36.990 --> 00:01:39.930 align:middle line:84%
forces for the oil
companies, started physically

00:01:39.930 --> 00:01:43.590 align:middle line:84%
attacking them with
police dogs and tear

00:01:43.590 --> 00:01:46.800 align:middle line:84%
gas and everything else,
I was asked to come up

00:01:46.800 --> 00:01:48.210 align:middle line:90%
to help try to solve that.

00:01:48.210 --> 00:01:51.270 align:middle line:84%
Because I had been co-counsel
for the Native American Rights

00:01:51.270 --> 00:01:52.930 align:middle line:90%
Committee for ACLU National

00:01:52.930 --> 00:01:53.730 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Ok

00:01:53.730 --> 00:01:57.220 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: Back in '73 during
the occupation of Wounded Knee.

00:01:57.220 --> 00:02:01.230 align:middle line:84%
And I was amicus counsel
with ACLU back then.

00:02:01.230 --> 00:02:02.030 align:middle line:90%
And so--

00:02:02.030 --> 00:02:04.238 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Oh, you go way back
into history, my friend.

00:02:04.238 --> 00:02:06.426 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: Yeah, well,
that was back in '73.

00:02:06.426 --> 00:02:08.550 align:middle line:10%
I had come off the Harvard
Civil Rights Law Review.

00:02:08.550 --> 00:02:10.590 align:middle line:10%
I was one of the founders of
the Harvard Civil Rights Law

00:02:10.590 --> 00:02:11.430 align:middle line:10%
Review.

00:02:11.430 --> 00:02:13.320 align:middle line:10%
And I had started
writing articles

00:02:13.320 --> 00:02:16.320 align:middle line:10%
about things that got me into
representing the New York

00:02:16.320 --> 00:02:18.720 align:middle line:10%
Times and the
Pentagon Papers case,

00:02:18.720 --> 00:02:20.312 align:middle line:10%
and did the case
that established

00:02:20.312 --> 00:02:22.770 align:middle line:10%
the right of journalists to
protect their confidential news

00:02:22.770 --> 00:02:23.940 align:middle line:10%
sources.

00:02:23.940 --> 00:02:26.640 align:middle line:84%
I did all those coming
out of Harvard Law School.

00:02:26.640 --> 00:02:29.580 align:middle line:84%
So I ended up being
asked to go in--

00:02:29.580 --> 00:02:33.120 align:middle line:84%
I was at F. Lee Bailey's
office, actually, at the time,

00:02:33.120 --> 00:02:36.330 align:middle line:84%
working on the
Watergate burglary case,

00:02:36.330 --> 00:02:38.730 align:middle line:84%
representing James
McCord, who wrote

00:02:38.730 --> 00:02:41.040 align:middle line:84%
the letter to Judge
Sirica, blowing the whistle

00:02:41.040 --> 00:02:42.120 align:middle line:90%
on the Plumbers.

00:02:42.120 --> 00:02:44.852 align:middle line:84%
So that's the kind of cases
that I tend to be involved in.

00:02:44.852 --> 00:02:46.060 align:middle line:90%
And I was asked to come out--

00:02:46.060 --> 00:02:47.210 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: None of
them high profile.

00:02:47.210 --> 00:02:48.042 align:middle line:90%
>>SHEEHAN: Yeah.

00:02:48.042 --> 00:02:49.440 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:02:49.440 --> 00:02:53.250 align:middle line:84%
Mainly involving media,
important like media

00:02:53.250 --> 00:02:56.430 align:middle line:84%
like this that can
actually get out to people

00:02:56.430 --> 00:02:59.700 align:middle line:84%
and play a role in
helping educate people

00:02:59.700 --> 00:03:02.730 align:middle line:84%
in the country
about major debates.

00:03:02.730 --> 00:03:05.250 align:middle line:84%
So these things are high
profile because they

00:03:05.250 --> 00:03:08.385 align:middle line:84%
tend to have two very
intense sides that

00:03:08.385 --> 00:03:10.140 align:middle line:84%
are confronting
each other with kind

00:03:10.140 --> 00:03:12.280 align:middle line:90%
of alternative views of reality.

00:03:12.280 --> 00:03:13.080 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Right.

00:03:13.080 --> 00:03:13.920 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: And so
what I try to do--

00:03:13.920 --> 00:03:14.940 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: There's no middle
ground there, either.

00:03:14.940 --> 00:03:17.340 align:middle line:10%
>>SHEEHAN: It is very difficult.
So what I try to do, I say,

00:03:17.340 --> 00:03:18.140 align:middle line:10%
look it.

00:03:18.140 --> 00:03:22.050 align:middle line:10%
Let's take a look at a
process that the federal rules

00:03:22.050 --> 00:03:25.110 align:middle line:10%
of civil procedure
are designed to try

00:03:25.110 --> 00:03:27.660 align:middle line:10%
to get at the information
on both sides,

00:03:27.660 --> 00:03:29.667 align:middle line:10%
get them up in
front of a jury so

00:03:29.667 --> 00:03:32.250 align:middle line:10%
that you can have regular people
put in the box with the jury.

00:03:32.250 --> 00:03:33.540 align:middle line:90%
And you follow the rules.

00:03:33.540 --> 00:03:36.009 align:middle line:84%
And you put all the
information in front of them.

00:03:36.009 --> 00:03:38.550 align:middle line:84%
And then you try to get regular
people who have common sense.

00:03:38.550 --> 00:03:42.480 align:middle line:84%
I have great confidence
in regular people

00:03:42.480 --> 00:03:44.670 align:middle line:84%
to be able to come to
intelligent judgment

00:03:44.670 --> 00:03:46.625 align:middle line:84%
when they get the
adequate information.

00:03:46.625 --> 00:03:48.750 align:middle line:84%
But what they have is they
have two different sides

00:03:48.750 --> 00:03:51.760 align:middle line:84%
in front of them,
combating with each other

00:03:51.760 --> 00:03:55.110 align:middle line:84%
and demonizing each
other and trying

00:03:55.110 --> 00:03:57.360 align:middle line:84%
to assert sets of facts
that are kind of completely

00:03:57.360 --> 00:03:58.609 align:middle line:90%
incompatible.

00:03:58.609 --> 00:04:00.150 align:middle line:84%
And so the poor jury
is sitting there

00:04:00.150 --> 00:04:01.909 align:middle line:90%
a lot of times going, oh, gee.

00:04:01.909 --> 00:04:03.450 align:middle line:84%
What am I supposed
to do, flip a coin

00:04:03.450 --> 00:04:05.560 align:middle line:84%
to decide who's telling
me the truth here?

00:04:05.560 --> 00:04:08.390 align:middle line:84%
And so what I try to do
is do something different.

00:04:08.390 --> 00:04:10.080 align:middle line:84%
And I try to get
in to say, look it.

00:04:10.080 --> 00:04:12.870 align:middle line:84%
There's going to be one
person in the courtroom

00:04:12.870 --> 00:04:17.279 align:middle line:84%
that you can totally depend
upon to tell you the truth.

00:04:17.279 --> 00:04:19.050 align:middle line:90%
That is what I'm here for.

00:04:19.050 --> 00:04:22.110 align:middle line:84%
And I'm usually in a position
what they call amicus,

00:04:22.110 --> 00:04:23.520 align:middle line:90%
which is called amicus curiae.

00:04:23.520 --> 00:04:26.280 align:middle line:84%
It's a friend of the
court who is here

00:04:26.280 --> 00:04:29.520 align:middle line:84%
to try to figure out
between these two disputing

00:04:29.520 --> 00:04:32.280 align:middle line:84%
parties what the
objective truth is here

00:04:32.280 --> 00:04:33.960 align:middle line:90%
and then share it with the jury.

00:04:33.960 --> 00:04:35.685 align:middle line:84%
And I've been
comparatively successful--

00:04:35.685 --> 00:04:36.810 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Good for you.

00:04:36.810 --> 00:04:38.560 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: In getting
the jury to say yes,

00:04:38.560 --> 00:04:40.680 align:middle line:84%
I believe that he knows
what he's talking about.

00:04:40.680 --> 00:04:42.660 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You recently
went to the Vatican,

00:04:42.660 --> 00:04:44.850 align:middle line:84%
dealing with a climate
change conference.

00:04:44.850 --> 00:04:46.390 align:middle line:90%
What was that all about?

00:04:46.390 --> 00:04:50.730 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: Well, as people
know, back in June of 2015,

00:04:50.730 --> 00:04:53.580 align:middle line:84%
Pope Francis, the
first Jesuit pope

00:04:53.580 --> 00:04:57.610 align:middle line:84%
in history, who's a
scientist, actually.

00:04:57.610 --> 00:04:58.970 align:middle line:90%
He's a professional scientist.

00:04:58.970 --> 00:04:59.854 align:middle line:90%
That's his PhD.

00:04:59.854 --> 00:05:01.020 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: He knows his stuff.

00:05:01.020 --> 00:05:02.490 align:middle line:90%
>>SHEEHAN: His PhD degree--

00:05:02.490 --> 00:05:03.990 align:middle line:84%
and he sat down
and said, look it.

00:05:03.990 --> 00:05:05.490 align:middle line:84%
There's this big
controversy going

00:05:05.490 --> 00:05:08.520 align:middle line:84%
on in the world about whether
global climate-- there's

00:05:08.520 --> 00:05:11.310 align:middle line:84%
no debate that global
climate change is happening.

00:05:11.310 --> 00:05:12.960 align:middle line:84%
The debate was about
what it's about.

00:05:12.960 --> 00:05:13.140 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: And how.

00:05:13.140 --> 00:05:14.610 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: Why is
this happening?

00:05:14.610 --> 00:05:16.020 align:middle line:90%
What seems to be going on?

00:05:16.020 --> 00:05:18.840 align:middle line:84%
And so he took this
comparatively measured

00:05:18.840 --> 00:05:20.450 align:middle line:90%
position, saying look it.

00:05:20.450 --> 00:05:23.370 align:middle line:84%
We're not saying that
there isn't other factors.

00:05:23.370 --> 00:05:26.220 align:middle line:84%
You have solar flares,
the changing temperatures,

00:05:26.220 --> 00:05:27.290 align:middle line:90%
shifting of our orbit.

00:05:27.290 --> 00:05:29.410 align:middle line:84%
And certainly, they're
contributing to this.

00:05:29.410 --> 00:05:31.560 align:middle line:84%
But the question we
have in front of us

00:05:31.560 --> 00:05:35.880 align:middle line:84%
is whether or not the
burning of fossil fuels--

00:05:35.880 --> 00:05:39.870 align:middle line:84%
and by the way, the massive
increase in eating red meat

00:05:39.870 --> 00:05:44.730 align:middle line:84%
and cutting down trees in the
equatorial jungles and growing

00:05:44.730 --> 00:05:50.160 align:middle line:84%
soybeans and generating
millions and millions of cattle

00:05:50.160 --> 00:05:54.420 align:middle line:84%
for Wendy's and
McDonald's and stuff

00:05:54.420 --> 00:05:57.969 align:middle line:84%
is generating flatus, actually,
of millions of cattle.

00:05:57.969 --> 00:05:59.010 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Who would think?

00:05:59.010 --> 00:06:00.840 align:middle line:90%
>>SHEEHAN: Who would think that?

00:06:00.840 --> 00:06:04.350 align:middle line:84%
But in fact, it's putting
millions of tons of methane gas

00:06:04.350 --> 00:06:05.770 align:middle line:90%
up into the atmosphere.

00:06:05.770 --> 00:06:09.360 align:middle line:84%
So his inquiry,
Jesuit inquiry, was

00:06:09.360 --> 00:06:13.320 align:middle line:84%
to try to determine whether
or not, to some degree,

00:06:13.320 --> 00:06:17.370 align:middle line:84%
the burning of fossil fuels
is putting extra carbon

00:06:17.370 --> 00:06:20.580 align:middle line:84%
dioxide and methane
into the atmosphere that

00:06:20.580 --> 00:06:24.700 align:middle line:84%
is accelerating and exacerbating
these other natural processes.

00:06:24.700 --> 00:06:25.500 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Exactly.

00:06:25.500 --> 00:06:29.580 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: And he came to the
conclusion that it really was.

00:06:29.580 --> 00:06:32.490 align:middle line:84%
And he said in light of this
fact, we've got a problem here,

00:06:32.490 --> 00:06:33.290 align:middle line:90%
he said.

00:06:33.290 --> 00:06:38.280 align:middle line:84%
Because the oil and coal and
oil and natural gas corporations

00:06:38.280 --> 00:06:43.255 align:middle line:84%
have hired a whole group
of public relations firms

00:06:43.255 --> 00:06:44.880 align:middle line:84%
and are paying them
millions of dollars

00:06:44.880 --> 00:06:47.910 align:middle line:84%
a year to actually
try to convince people

00:06:47.910 --> 00:06:50.850 align:middle line:84%
that there is no significant
contribution being

00:06:50.850 --> 00:06:55.370 align:middle line:84%
made to this process by the oil,
chemical, and coal companies.

00:06:55.370 --> 00:06:56.760 align:middle line:90%
And it's just not true.

00:06:56.760 --> 00:06:57.760 align:middle line:90%
And so he said, look it.

00:06:57.760 --> 00:07:01.860 align:middle line:84%
I am morally obliged to try
to use my office to share

00:07:01.860 --> 00:07:03.630 align:middle line:90%
this information with people.

00:07:03.630 --> 00:07:05.610 align:middle line:10%
And what people
need to understand

00:07:05.610 --> 00:07:09.150 align:middle line:10%
is that these public
relations firms

00:07:09.150 --> 00:07:12.030 align:middle line:10%
are the same companies that
were hired by the tobacco

00:07:12.030 --> 00:07:13.110 align:middle line:10%
companies--

00:07:13.110 --> 00:07:14.130 align:middle line:10%
exact same companies.

00:07:14.130 --> 00:07:14.670 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Right.

00:07:14.670 --> 00:07:15.710 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: They were
hired to convince people--

00:07:15.710 --> 00:07:16.830 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Tobacco
doesn't cause cancer.

00:07:16.830 --> 00:07:19.660 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: To convince people
that smoking tobacco doesn't--

00:07:19.660 --> 00:07:22.380 align:middle line:84%
smoking their cigarettes, more
importantly-- doesn't cause

00:07:22.380 --> 00:07:23.970 align:middle line:90%
cancer, which it does.

00:07:23.970 --> 00:07:24.950 align:middle line:90%
And it did.

00:07:24.950 --> 00:07:25.830 align:middle line:90%
And it took years.

00:07:25.830 --> 00:07:29.400 align:middle line:84%
It took like 25 years of people
trying to litigate against this

00:07:29.400 --> 00:07:30.960 align:middle line:90%
to get this established.

00:07:30.960 --> 00:07:33.915 align:middle line:84%
And my constitutional law,
Professor Larry Tribe,

00:07:33.915 --> 00:07:35.820 align:middle line:84%
at Harvard Law School
is the one that

00:07:35.820 --> 00:07:39.000 align:middle line:84%
finally litigated that case
to success against the tobacco

00:07:39.000 --> 00:07:39.900 align:middle line:90%
companies.

00:07:39.900 --> 00:07:41.441 align:middle line:84%
And so that's how
I know that they're

00:07:41.441 --> 00:07:42.530 align:middle line:90%
the same exact companies.

00:07:42.530 --> 00:07:44.040 align:middle line:90%
And they're very slick.

00:07:44.040 --> 00:07:45.560 align:middle line:90%
And they're very convincing.

00:07:45.560 --> 00:07:47.250 align:middle line:84%
And they put out
millions of dollars

00:07:47.250 --> 00:07:50.360 align:middle line:84%
to generate videos, kind
of propaganda videos.

00:07:50.360 --> 00:07:51.160 align:middle line:90%


00:07:51.160 --> 00:07:52.320 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: [INAUDIBLE].

00:07:52.320 --> 00:07:53.425 align:middle line:90%
>>SHEEHAN: Oh, yeah.

00:07:53.425 --> 00:07:58.890 align:middle line:84%
And the thing is is that because
so many people in our country,

00:07:58.890 --> 00:08:01.400 align:middle line:84%
for completely
legitimate reasons,

00:08:01.400 --> 00:08:04.360 align:middle line:84%
have come to distrust
the government

00:08:04.360 --> 00:08:08.955 align:middle line:84%
and to distrust the Catholic
church, that in fact--

00:08:08.955 --> 00:08:10.330 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: For a
number of reasons.

00:08:10.330 --> 00:08:12.746 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: For a number of
reasons-- and what they've done

00:08:12.746 --> 00:08:15.610 align:middle line:84%
is they're at sea of trying to
figure out what the truth is.

00:08:15.610 --> 00:08:18.670 align:middle line:84%
And if they are confronted
by slick, million dollar

00:08:18.670 --> 00:08:23.770 align:middle line:84%
commercials, propaganda
pieces, they say, oh, OK.

00:08:23.770 --> 00:08:25.430 align:middle line:90%
I think that's true.

00:08:25.430 --> 00:08:30.650 align:middle line:84%
And what Pope Francis was trying
to do, along with, by the way,

00:08:30.650 --> 00:08:34.960 align:middle line:84%
virtually every other one of the
major religious denominations

00:08:34.960 --> 00:08:37.600 align:middle line:84%
in the world, are
saying that look,

00:08:37.600 --> 00:08:40.669 align:middle line:84%
this is a terribly dangerous
problem here that we've got,

00:08:40.669 --> 00:08:44.100 align:middle line:84%
that we are facing a
potential catastrophe.

00:08:44.100 --> 00:08:46.789 align:middle line:84%
United States Defense
Department knows it.

00:08:46.789 --> 00:08:49.330 align:middle line:84%
United States Defense Department
is making all kinds of plans

00:08:49.330 --> 00:08:53.320 align:middle line:84%
and mobilizing to deal with the
major social disruption that's

00:08:53.320 --> 00:08:55.867 align:middle line:84%
going to be caused if
we don't slow this down.

00:08:55.867 --> 00:08:56.950 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: It will be chaos.

00:08:56.950 --> 00:08:58.366 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: It will
be total chaos.

00:08:58.366 --> 00:08:59.640 align:middle line:90%
And we see it happening now.

00:08:59.640 --> 00:09:04.390 align:middle line:84%
And what we see up at Standing
Rock, up in North Dakota,

00:09:04.390 --> 00:09:07.450 align:middle line:84%
we see a microcosm
of the future.

00:09:07.450 --> 00:09:10.360 align:middle line:84%
Because what we've seen here
is that the United States,

00:09:10.360 --> 00:09:12.640 align:middle line:84%
now under the present
administration,

00:09:12.640 --> 00:09:17.330 align:middle line:84%
has mobilized and provided
military equipment to the state

00:09:17.330 --> 00:09:19.060 align:middle line:84%
National Guard,
the state police,

00:09:19.060 --> 00:09:21.160 align:middle line:84%
to the sheriff's departments
and everything, where

00:09:21.160 --> 00:09:24.220 align:middle line:84%
they basically mobilized what
