started protesting,

00:09:43.720 --> 00:09:45.430 align:middle line:10%
because they came
to the conclusion

00:09:45.430 --> 00:09:48.370 align:middle line:10%
it was a threat to
their water, the company

00:09:48.370 --> 00:09:52.600 align:middle line:10%
decided to put it right
down onto the great Sioux

00:09:52.600 --> 00:09:55.195 align:middle line:10%
reservation, where it's
80% Native American.

00:09:55.195 --> 00:09:56.570 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And they
went ballistic.

00:09:56.570 --> 00:09:58.810 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: And the people
said, wait a second.

00:09:58.810 --> 00:10:00.970 align:middle line:84%
There are regulations,
environmental regulations,

00:10:00.970 --> 00:10:04.120 align:middle line:84%
and everything that prohibit
you from racially discriminating

00:10:04.120 --> 00:10:08.500 align:middle line:84%
by putting a dangerous facility
down in the minority community.

00:10:08.500 --> 00:10:12.370 align:middle line:84%
Because the fact is for 25
years, that's been going on--

00:10:12.370 --> 00:10:16.360 align:middle line:84%
waste disposals, toxic dumps,
everything-- all end up right

00:10:16.360 --> 00:10:18.226 align:middle line:90%
next to minority communities.

00:10:18.226 --> 00:10:19.600 align:middle line:84%
And so there are
regulations that

00:10:19.600 --> 00:10:21.480 align:middle line:84%
have been passed to tell
them to stop doing that.

00:10:21.480 --> 00:10:22.600 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Who would
know that, Daniel?

00:10:22.600 --> 00:10:23.560 align:middle line:90%
Not a lot of people know that.

00:10:23.560 --> 00:10:25.226 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: No, no,
that's exactly right.

00:10:25.226 --> 00:10:26.470 align:middle line:90%
But Chase Iron Eyes knew it.

00:10:26.470 --> 00:10:30.470 align:middle line:10%
Chase Iron Eyes, a full,
lifelong member of the Oglala--

00:10:30.470 --> 00:10:35.240 align:middle line:10%
or excuse, Standing Rock Sioux
Hunkpapa, Sitting Bull's tribe,

00:10:35.240 --> 00:10:36.040 align:middle line:10%
knew it.

00:10:36.040 --> 00:10:37.480 align:middle line:90%
Because he was a trained lawyer.

00:10:37.480 --> 00:10:39.630 align:middle line:90%
He said this, is totally crazy.

00:10:39.630 --> 00:10:41.500 align:middle line:84%
These people can't
just move a pipeline

00:10:41.500 --> 00:10:44.890 align:middle line:84%
from a 93% white
community down to an 80%

00:10:44.890 --> 00:10:46.540 align:middle line:84%
Native American
community and put it

00:10:46.540 --> 00:10:50.315 align:middle line:84%
right under their sole
source of drinking water.

00:10:50.315 --> 00:10:51.190 align:middle line:90%
That's what they did.

00:10:51.190 --> 00:10:54.220 align:middle line:84%
They drilled it right under
their drinking water source.

00:10:54.220 --> 00:10:58.020 align:middle line:84%
And so the Sunoco Corporation
that is building it there--

00:10:58.020 --> 00:11:01.570 align:middle line:84%
they're behind the Energy
Transfer Partners--

00:11:01.570 --> 00:11:03.610 align:middle line:84%
they built it right
under that place.

00:11:03.610 --> 00:11:10.120 align:middle line:84%
They have had, since
2010, 200, 200 oil leaks

00:11:10.120 --> 00:11:12.310 align:middle line:90%
from their pipelines.

00:11:12.310 --> 00:11:13.660 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Seeping in this water.

00:11:13.660 --> 00:11:15.410 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: Seeping
into the ground water--

00:11:15.410 --> 00:11:17.020 align:middle line:90%
and we know that.

00:11:17.020 --> 00:11:18.610 align:middle line:90%
But they don't tell people that.

00:11:18.610 --> 00:11:19.890 align:middle line:90%
And they lie about it.

00:11:19.890 --> 00:11:23.560 align:middle line:84%
My job is to dig out the
objective information

00:11:23.560 --> 00:11:26.600 align:middle line:84%
to provide to a jury so
they'll know what that is.

00:11:26.600 --> 00:11:29.260 align:middle line:84%
And so what they did is they
swept in, because Chase Iron

00:11:29.260 --> 00:11:34.030 align:middle line:84%
Eyes, who was the Democratic
Party nominee for the United

00:11:34.030 --> 00:11:38.290 align:middle line:84%
States Congress from North
Dakota, the only congressman--

00:11:38.290 --> 00:11:39.970 align:middle line:90%
they only have one congressman.

00:11:39.970 --> 00:11:42.490 align:middle line:84%
He was the nominee for
the Democratic Party.

00:11:42.490 --> 00:11:45.700 align:middle line:84%
And he is a lawyer for
the Standing Rock Sioux

00:11:45.700 --> 00:11:46.570 align:middle line:90%
reservation.

00:11:46.570 --> 00:11:47.800 align:middle line:90%
And he organized.

00:11:47.800 --> 00:11:51.970 align:middle line:84%
He said people should come,
come here, and sit peacefully,

00:11:51.970 --> 00:11:54.400 align:middle line:84%
prayerfully,
respectfully, and just

00:11:54.400 --> 00:11:58.600 align:middle line:84%
sit in the pathway of the
pipeline on land that we own.

00:11:58.600 --> 00:11:59.400 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Right.

00:11:59.400 --> 00:12:00.200 align:middle line:90%
It's ours.

00:12:00.200 --> 00:12:02.960 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: That we have
owned for 1,000 years.

00:12:02.960 --> 00:12:04.460 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: By treaty
and right, right?

00:12:04.460 --> 00:12:05.668 align:middle line:90%
>>SHEEHAN: Yes, that's right.

00:12:05.668 --> 00:12:09.160 align:middle line:84%
And so-- but the
administration said, oh, no.

00:12:09.160 --> 00:12:12.130 align:middle line:84%
And it turns out that
high level officials

00:12:12.130 --> 00:12:16.930 align:middle line:84%
