partners in the energy transfer

00:12:16.930 --> 00:12:18.120 align:middle line:90%
partner corporation.

00:12:18.120 --> 00:12:18.370 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Go figure.

00:12:18.370 --> 00:12:19.220 align:middle line:90%
>>SHEEHAN: Business partners.

00:12:19.220 --> 00:12:19.970 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Go figure.

00:12:19.970 --> 00:12:20.240 align:middle line:90%
>>SHEEHAN: Yeah.

00:12:20.240 --> 00:12:20.680 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Right.

00:12:20.680 --> 00:12:22.360 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: Yeah, including
Rick Perry, the head

00:12:22.360 --> 00:12:23.260 align:middle line:90%
of the Department of Energy.

00:12:23.260 --> 00:12:24.820 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Now let's get
back to climate change.

00:12:24.820 --> 00:12:25.120 align:middle line:90%
>>SHEEHAN: Yes.

00:12:25.120 --> 00:12:27.400 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I have long
believed that the earth goes

00:12:27.400 --> 00:12:31.540 align:middle line:84%
through cycles, that we've had
climate change in the dinosaur

00:12:31.540 --> 00:12:34.330 align:middle line:84%
era, that things
are going to change.

00:12:34.330 --> 00:12:39.150 align:middle line:84%
But I do believe that mankind
is contributing to things,

00:12:39.150 --> 00:12:41.830 align:middle line:90%
maybe speeding things up.

00:12:41.830 --> 00:12:43.452 align:middle line:90%
What do we do about that?

00:12:43.452 --> 00:12:45.410 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: Well, what we
do is we say, look it,

00:12:45.410 --> 00:12:48.790 align:middle line:84%
is there some alternative means
that we can have for generating

00:12:48.790 --> 00:12:52.120 align:middle line:84%
the kind of electrical energy,
energy for our cars and stuff,

00:12:52.120 --> 00:12:54.970 align:middle line:84%
is there some alternative that
we can engage in collectively

00:12:54.970 --> 00:12:55.780 align:middle line:90%
and intelligently?

00:12:55.780 --> 00:12:56.620 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Sooner than later.

00:12:56.620 --> 00:12:58.180 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: Sooner,
so that we don't

00:12:58.180 --> 00:13:02.860 align:middle line:84%
have to keep on encouraging and
facilitating and subsidizing

00:13:02.860 --> 00:13:05.420 align:middle line:84%
the actual destruction
of the planet.

00:13:05.420 --> 00:13:07.325 align:middle line:84%
Because what they're
saying here is that--

00:13:07.325 --> 00:13:10.580 align:middle line:84%
and this is what the scientific
community is saying--

00:13:10.580 --> 00:13:14.420 align:middle line:84%
2,500 scientists
from around the world

00:13:14.420 --> 00:13:16.380 align:middle line:84%
have all come together
to discuss this.

00:13:16.380 --> 00:13:21.470 align:middle line:84%
And they say that they believe
that the catastrophic dimension

00:13:21.470 --> 00:13:23.800 align:middle line:84%
of the gradual climate
change that is going on,

00:13:23.800 --> 00:13:27.590 align:middle line:84%
the catastrophic dimension
is being proximately caused

00:13:27.590 --> 00:13:32.120 align:middle line:84%
by the burning of coal in
gasoline, in oil, crude oil,

00:13:32.120 --> 00:13:37.100 align:middle line:84%
in natural gas, as a means
of providing our electricity

00:13:37.100 --> 00:13:39.830 align:middle line:84%
and for fueling
our cars, that we

00:13:39.830 --> 00:13:41.480 align:middle line:90%
should decide not to do that.

00:13:41.480 --> 00:13:43.830 align:middle line:84%
What we should do is
we should organize

00:13:43.830 --> 00:13:49.670 align:middle line:84%
how to get solar power,
hydroelectric power,

00:13:49.670 --> 00:13:52.160 align:middle line:90%
thermal power--

00:13:52.160 --> 00:13:53.960 align:middle line:84%
all of these different
kinds of energy,

00:13:53.960 --> 00:13:56.390 align:middle line:84%
which are technologically
available to us.

00:13:56.390 --> 00:13:59.540 align:middle line:84%
Why don't we, like we
used to-- we subsidized

00:13:59.540 --> 00:14:01.490 align:middle line:84%
the development of
oil, the oil depletion

00:14:01.490 --> 00:14:04.400 align:middle line:84%
allowances that all have
gone on for decades,

00:14:04.400 --> 00:14:07.160 align:middle line:84%
subsidizing the development
of the oil corporations.

00:14:07.160 --> 00:14:10.550 align:middle line:84%
Why don't we shift that money
into developing clean energy?

00:14:10.550 --> 00:14:12.050 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Some of
the media out there

00:14:12.050 --> 00:14:14.660 align:middle line:84%
tries to present
the news to give us

00:14:14.660 --> 00:14:17.690 align:middle line:84%
all that view of what's
going on with climate change,

00:14:17.690 --> 00:14:19.600 align:middle line:90%
like the BBC.

00:14:19.600 --> 00:14:22.160 align:middle line:84%
>> Considered the world's
most authoritative assessment

00:14:22.160 --> 00:14:26.390 align:middle line:84%
of climate change, this latest
IPCC report has taken input

00:14:26.390 --> 00:14:30.230 align:middle line:84%
from more than 800 experts
citing more than 9,000

00:14:30.230 --> 00:14:31.910 align:middle line:90%
scientific studies.

00:14:31.910 --> 00:14:33.810 align:middle line:90%
It's published in three parts.

00:14:33.810 --> 00:14:37.350 align:middle line:84%
The first about the science of
climate change comes on Friday.

00:14:37.350 --> 00:14:38.990 align:middle line:84%
The others about
the impacts and what

00:14:38.990 --> 00:14:41.960 align:middle line:84%
can be done to mitigate
it follow next year.

00:14:41.960 --> 00:14:43.610 align:middle line:84%
Since the last
report, scientists

00:14:43.610 --> 00:14:46.730 align:middle line:84%
have had six years to
gather and examine more data

00:14:46.730 --> 00:14:48.560 align:middle line:84%
and to refine computer
models designed

00:14:48.560 --> 00:14:50.520 align:middle line:90%
to project into the future.

00:14:50.520 --> 00:14:51.590 align:middle line:90%
>> That's good.

00:14:51.590 --> 00:14:54.170 align:middle line:84%
>> They'll draw on new data,
including on the warming

00:14:54.170 --> 00:14:55.580 align:middle line:90%
of our oceans.

00:14:55.580 --> 00:14:58.100 align:middle line:84%
Ocean temperature monitoring
has been revolutionized

00:14:58.100 --> 00:15:01.070 align:middle line:84%
by a worldwide network of
floating observatories called

00:15:01.070 --> 00:15:02.870 align:middle line:90%
the Argo network.

00:15:02.870 --> 00:15:05.270 align:middle line:84%
Many scientists believe that
atmospheric temperatures

00:15:05.270 --> 00:15:07.790 align:middle line:84%
have been rising more
slowly in recent years

00:15:07.790 --> 00:15:10.550 align:middle line:84%
because more heat is
being stored in the ocean.

00:15:10.550 --> 00:15:13.850 align:middle line:84%
And since sea water expands as
it warms, understanding this

00:15:13.850 --> 00:15:16.490 align:middle line:84%
will enable scientists to
better predict and plan

00:15:16.490 --> 00:15:18.120 align:middle line:90%
for sea level rise.

00:15:18.120 --> 00:15:20.720 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: So, Daniel, where are
we headed with all of this?

00:15:20.720 --> 00:15:21.080 align:middle line:90%
>>SHEEHAN: Well--

00:15:21.080 --> 00:15:22.370 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: What happens next?

00:15:22.370 --> 00:15:24.140 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: I think
what we have discovered

00:15:24.140 --> 00:15:25.910 align:middle line:90%
at our at our office, we have--

00:15:25.910 --> 00:15:28.744 align:middle line:84%
I have been working with
Jerry Brown, former Jesuit--

00:15:28.744 --> 00:15:31.160 align:middle line:84%
as you know, I was the chief
counsel for the United States

00:15:31.160 --> 00:15:33.890 align:middle line:84%
Jesuit headquarters in their
social ministry office,

00:15:33.890 --> 00:15:36.650 align:middle line:84%
trying to deal with public
policy issues like this.

00:15:36.650 --> 00:15:40.280 align:middle line:84%
And Jerry Brown has worked in
California, where they've now

00:15:40.280 --> 00:15:44.090 align:middle line:84%
passed the statute which
actually authorizes counties

00:15:44.090 --> 00:15:46.370 align:middle line:84%
to join together to
actually purchase

00:15:46.370 --> 00:15:50.210 align:middle line:84%
clean sources of energy and
to provide those at a lower

00:15:50.210 --> 00:15:54.320 align:middle line:84%
price for all the people who
would otherwise be purchasing

00:15:54.320 --> 00:15:56.252 align:middle line:84%
energy that is generated
by coal burning.

00:15:56.252 --> 00:15:57.710 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Right--
at a higher price.

00:15:57.710 --> 00:15:59.760 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: Yeah,
at a higher price.

00:15:59.760 --> 00:16:02.760 align:middle line:84%
And so this is a thing called
a community choice energy

00:16:02.760 --> 00:16:03.560 align:middle line:90%
company.

00:16:03.560 --> 00:16:04.670 align:middle line:90%
And it's publicly owned.

00:16:04.670 --> 00:16:06.290 align:middle line:84%
It's not owned by
private shareholders

00:16:06.290 --> 00:16:09.300 align:middle line:84%
or driving them
to their profits.

00:16:09.300 --> 00:16:12.020 align:middle line:84%
And so we have now
organized all of that.

00:16:12.020 --> 00:16:14.720 align:middle line:84%
And we've got the three
counties around Monterey Bay--

00:16:14.720 --> 00:16:17.070 align:middle line:90%
Pebble Beach and all that area.

00:16:17.070 --> 00:16:18.662 align:middle line:10%
We've gotten all
three counties--

00:16:18.662 --> 00:16:20.370 align:middle line:10%
Santa Cruz County,
San Bernardino County,

00:16:20.370 --> 00:16:21.770 align:middle line:10%
and Monterey County--

00:16:21.770 --> 00:16:25.640 align:middle line:10%
we've gotten the Catholic
Diocese to actually give loans

00:16:25.640 --> 00:16:27.350 align:middle line:10%
to all the Catholic
churches to put

00:16:27.350 --> 00:16:30.260 align:middle line:10%
solar panels on
all their schools

00:16:30.260 --> 00:16:32.632 align:middle line:10%
and all of their churches.

00:16:32.632 --> 00:16:35.090 align:middle line:84%
And we've gotten the Union of
American Hebrew congregations

00:16:35.090 --> 00:16:38.120 align:middle line:84%
who've joined together with
us to do this for the temples.

00:16:38.120 --> 00:16:40.130 align:middle line:84%
We've gotten the Buddhist
communities to join.

00:16:40.130 --> 00:16:43.040 align:middle line:84%
And now the Methodist Church,
United Methodist Church Board

00:16:43.040 --> 00:16:45.100 align:middle line:84%
of Homeland Ministries
is on board.

00:16:45.100 --> 00:16:48.740 align:middle line:84%
We've shown that we can reduce
the amount of global greenhouse

00:16:48.740 --> 00:16:52.610 align:middle line:84%
gas emissions in those
three counties by 90%.

00:16:52.610 --> 00:16:54.260 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Oh, that's
astronomical.

00:16:54.260 --> 00:16:55.695 align:middle line:90%
>>SHEEHAN: Within 10 years.

00:16:55.695 --> 00:16:56.110 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Huge.

00:16:56.110 --> 00:16:57.610 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: And what
that will-- that

00:16:57.610 --> 00:17:00.270 align:middle line:84%
will meet the requests of
the International Panel

00:17:00.270 --> 00:17:02.660 align:middle line:90%
on Governmental Climate Change.

00:17:02.660 --> 00:17:05.240 align:middle line:84%
We can meet the
standards to stave off

00:17:05.240 --> 00:17:09.410 align:middle line:84%
these catastrophic events that
are being predicted by 2,500

00:17:09.410 --> 00:17:10.619 align:middle line:90%
scientists around the world.

00:17:10.619 --> 00:17:13.490 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And these predictions
are pretty soon, aren't they?

00:17:13.490 --> 00:17:15.230 align:middle line:90%
>>SHEEHAN: These are very soon.

00:17:15.230 --> 00:17:21.349 align:middle line:84%
If we don't reduce by
70% the annual rate

00:17:21.349 --> 00:17:23.119 align:middle line:84%
of global greenhouse
gas emissions.

00:17:23.119 --> 00:17:24.079 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That is happening now.

00:17:24.079 --> 00:17:25.454 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: That
is happening now.

00:17:25.454 --> 00:17:29.390 align:middle line:10%
If we don't reduce
that by 2025 by 70%,

00:17:29.390 --> 00:17:32.540 align:middle line:10%
we're going to be
wedded to catastrophe.

00:17:32.540 --> 00:17:35.330 align:middle line:10%
They detail what
the catastrophe is--

00:17:35.330 --> 00:17:38.900 align:middle line:10%
the rise of 6 and
1/2 feet by 2100

00:17:38.900 --> 00:17:41.317 align:middle line:10%
of the average sea
level around the world.

00:17:41.317 --> 00:17:43.150 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Which wipes
out our coastal cities.

00:17:43.150 --> 00:17:44.150 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: Because
as they've mentioned,

00:17:44.150 --> 00:17:46.670 align:middle line:84%
the BBC, that increased--
the heating of the ocean

00:17:46.670 --> 00:17:51.740 align:middle line:84%
expands the ocean so
that it will inundate up

00:17:51.740 --> 00:17:54.960 align:middle line:84%
to 10 miles of the coastlines
of the entire world, where

00:17:54.960 --> 00:17:57.020 align:middle line:90%
63% of all the people live.

00:17:57.020 --> 00:17:58.310 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Yeah, gone.

00:17:58.310 --> 00:17:59.920 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: And they
have to evacuate.

00:17:59.920 --> 00:18:02.630 align:middle line:84%
And not only that, but it's
melting the polar ice caps.

00:18:02.630 --> 00:18:05.720 align:middle line:84%
You saw the pictures of
the ice caps melting.

00:18:05.720 --> 00:18:09.840 align:middle line:84%
And that is adding fresh
water into the sea.

00:18:09.840 --> 00:18:12.890 align:middle line:84%
We're changing the density
of the sea from salt water

