we're going to take

00:46:03.640 --> 00:46:08.590 align:middle line:84%
all the steps necessary to
stop the corporate takeover

00:46:08.590 --> 00:46:11.770 align:middle line:84%
of our government, our
democratic institutions,

00:46:11.770 --> 00:46:15.010 align:middle line:84%
and our planet, and
our planet's future,

00:46:15.010 --> 00:46:21.395 align:middle line:84%
by some coupon clipping
shareholders in the oil, coal,

00:46:21.395 --> 00:46:22.270 align:middle line:90%
and gas corporations.

00:46:22.270 --> 00:46:24.520 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Is there any
middle ground here, Daniel?

00:46:24.520 --> 00:46:27.305 align:middle line:84%
Is there anything that can be
worked out with both sides?

00:46:27.305 --> 00:46:29.230 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: Oh, yes,
there definitely is.

00:46:29.230 --> 00:46:32.650 align:middle line:84%
All you have to do is
get those corporations

00:46:32.650 --> 00:46:36.070 align:middle line:84%
to agree to invest in
alternative clean energy

00:46:36.070 --> 00:46:36.870 align:middle line:90%
sources.

00:46:36.870 --> 00:46:37.970 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: It seems simple.

00:46:37.970 --> 00:46:40.261 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: They have billions
and billions and billions

00:46:40.261 --> 00:46:41.920 align:middle line:90%
of dollars of profits.

00:46:41.920 --> 00:46:44.890 align:middle line:84%
But instead of passing them
off to the stockholders

00:46:44.890 --> 00:46:46.930 align:middle line:84%
and letting them buy
another summer place,

00:46:46.930 --> 00:46:50.360 align:middle line:84%
reinvest that income into
developing alternative energy

00:46:50.360 --> 00:46:51.160 align:middle line:90%
sources.

00:46:51.160 --> 00:46:53.571 align:middle line:84%
And they can make billions
of dollars of profit.

00:46:53.571 --> 00:46:55.570 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And get great
publicity to boot, right?

00:46:55.570 --> 00:46:58.192 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: Absolutely,
absolutely.

00:46:58.192 --> 00:46:59.650 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: So why
don't they do that?

00:46:59.650 --> 00:47:01.066 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: Because
they don't want

00:47:01.066 --> 00:47:05.110 align:middle line:84%
to forego the short-term
profit of the materials

00:47:05.110 --> 00:47:07.960 align:middle line:84%
that they've already laid
claim to in the ground.

00:47:07.960 --> 00:47:12.550 align:middle line:84%
The reality is most of that
oil is in Saudi Arabia.

00:47:12.550 --> 00:47:13.840 align:middle line:90%
Or it's in such crude form.

00:47:13.840 --> 00:47:14.320 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Or Iraq.

00:47:14.320 --> 00:47:16.420 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: Or it's in such
crude form up in Canada

00:47:16.420 --> 00:47:18.490 align:middle line:84%
that they have to pipe
it through pipelines.

00:47:18.490 --> 00:47:20.450 align:middle line:84%
One thing to remember
in closing is

00:47:20.450 --> 00:47:23.890 align:middle line:84%
that not one single
drop of that oil

00:47:23.890 --> 00:47:25.717 align:middle line:84%
is coming through
the XL pipeline.

00:47:25.717 --> 00:47:26.800 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Doesn't go to us.

00:47:26.800 --> 00:47:28.216 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: Doesn't
come to relieve

00:47:28.216 --> 00:47:30.890 align:middle line:84%
any of the energy needs of
anybody in the United States.

00:47:30.890 --> 00:47:30.998 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Yeah.

00:47:30.998 --> 00:47:32.210 align:middle line:84%
It goes to Japan and
every place else.

00:47:32.210 --> 00:47:33.501 align:middle line:90%
>>SHEEHAN: It's all being sold.

00:47:33.501 --> 00:47:35.629 align:middle line:84%
It's all being sold on
the international market.

00:47:35.629 --> 00:47:36.795 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Yeah, at big bucks.

00:47:36.795 --> 00:47:38.200 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: At big
bucks for those

00:47:38.200 --> 00:47:42.250 align:middle line:84%
shareholders-- doesn't help
one single unit of energy

00:47:42.250 --> 00:47:43.900 align:middle line:90%
get generated in our country.

00:47:43.900 --> 00:47:47.080 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Do legislators
have the ability legally

00:47:47.080 --> 00:47:49.310 align:middle line:90%
to legislate morality?

00:47:49.310 --> 00:47:51.520 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: There's
a special form,

00:47:51.520 --> 00:47:55.480 align:middle line:84%
or what they call mode
of ethical reasoning,

00:47:55.480 --> 00:47:57.700 align:middle line:84%
that makes this
completely legitimate.

00:47:57.700 --> 00:48:01.150 align:middle line:84%
And it's related to a spiritual
perspective that is not

00:48:01.150 --> 00:48:03.280 align:middle line:90%
fully understood by people.

00:48:03.280 --> 00:48:07.270 align:middle line:84%
Because frankly, the
Roman Catholic Church,

00:48:07.270 --> 00:48:12.930 align:middle line:84%
when it ascended to power
in the third century AD,

00:48:12.930 --> 00:48:16.870 align:middle line:84%
that 99% of all the people
under their jurisdiction

00:48:16.870 --> 00:48:18.290 align:middle line:90%
couldn't read or write.

00:48:18.290 --> 00:48:20.920 align:middle line:84%
And so that they
simplified, and simplified,

00:48:20.920 --> 00:48:24.700 align:middle line:84%
and simplified a more complex
understanding of spirituality.

00:48:24.700 --> 00:48:28.960 align:middle line:84%
The bottom line is, is that
the spirituality that I'm

00:48:28.960 --> 00:48:32.680 align:middle line:84%
talking about is the fact
that if you sit at night

00:48:32.680 --> 00:48:36.850 align:middle line:84%
and look up into the sky
and pick out a distant star,

00:48:36.850 --> 00:48:39.557 align:middle line:84%
and you realize that we now
know they are planets orbiting--

00:48:39.557 --> 00:48:40.390 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: All around.

00:48:40.390 --> 00:48:41.420 align:middle line:90%
>>SHEEHAN: Orbiting these--

00:48:41.420 --> 00:48:42.253 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: All around.

00:48:42.253 --> 00:48:45.150 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: There other living
civilizations on those stars,

00:48:45.150 --> 00:48:46.120 align:middle line:90%
on those planets.

00:48:46.120 --> 00:48:49.600 align:middle line:84%
And they look down at
us and try to understand

00:48:49.600 --> 00:48:52.450 align:middle line:84%
how it is that we're
conducting ourselves.

00:48:52.450 --> 00:48:55.330 align:middle line:84%
Just think in terms of
conducting yourself in a way

00:48:55.330 --> 00:48:56.920 align:middle line:84%
that you could
reasonably support

00:48:56.920 --> 00:49:00.210 align:middle line:84%
and defend by explaining
how we conduct ourselves.

00:49:00.210 --> 00:49:01.180 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: We can't.

00:49:01.180 --> 00:49:02.440 align:middle line:90%
>>SHEEHAN: But we can.

00:49:02.440 --> 00:49:06.310 align:middle line:84%
All spirituality is, is getting
a higher and higher and higher

00:49:06.310 --> 00:49:09.580 align:middle line:84%
level of consciousness from
the perspective of which you

00:49:09.580 --> 00:49:11.830 align:middle line:90%
make your judgments.

00:49:11.830 --> 00:49:14.870 align:middle line:84%
And so that you can do
this without having to say,

00:49:14.870 --> 00:49:17.571 align:middle line:84%
oh, there's some big,
white, anthropomorphic male

00:49:17.571 --> 00:49:19.570 align:middle line:84%
being sitting on a throne
somewhere telling us--

00:49:19.570 --> 00:49:19.750 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Dictating to us.

00:49:19.750 --> 00:49:21.125 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: What
to do, dictating,

00:49:21.125 --> 00:49:23.800 align:middle line:84%
or some pope somewhere,
or some bishop somewhere,

00:49:23.800 --> 00:49:25.614 align:middle line:90%
or some clergyman somewhere.

00:49:25.614 --> 00:49:27.280 align:middle line:84%
No, that's not what
we're talking about.

00:49:27.280 --> 00:49:28.696 align:middle line:84%
What we're talking
about is people

00:49:28.696 --> 00:49:31.050 align:middle line:84%
having a higher and higher
level of consciousness.

00:49:31.050 --> 00:49:33.220 align:middle line:84%
And that's completely
authorized.

00:49:33.220 --> 00:49:35.590 align:middle line:84%
There's nothing
unlawful about that.

00:49:35.590 --> 00:49:38.200 align:middle line:84%
And what we're saying is
that if you have a broader

00:49:38.200 --> 00:49:41.260 align:middle line:84%
perspective on reality
and what's going on,

00:49:41.260 --> 00:49:44.200 align:middle line:84%
that is a mode of ethical
reasoning from the perspective

00:49:44.200 --> 00:49:46.150 align:middle line:90%
of which you can legislate.

00:49:46.150 --> 00:49:48.100 align:middle line:84%
And that's all that
we're advocating here.

00:49:48.100 --> 00:49:52.310 align:middle line:10%
The fact that that happens to
correlate with spirituality

00:49:52.310 --> 00:49:55.030 align:middle line:10%
in an ever-increasing
spiritual consciousness

00:49:55.030 --> 00:49:57.400 align:middle line:10%
is an important
thing that we just

00:49:57.400 --> 00:50:00.250 align:middle line:10%
need to help get the churches
and synagogues and temples

00:50:00.250 --> 00:50:03.460 align:middle line:10%
and others to explain that
to more and more people,

00:50:03.460 --> 00:50:06.067 align:middle line:10%
now that people can read
and think more effectively.

00:50:06.067 --> 00:50:07.150 align:middle line:90%
That's what we need to do.

00:50:07.150 --> 00:50:09.895 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What would the
pope like to happen?

00:50:09.895 --> 00:50:12.020 align:middle line:10%
>>SHEEHAN: The pope would
like to happen-- in fact,

00:50:12.020 --> 00:50:14.360 align:middle line:10%
the pope has, in
fact, reached out now

00:50:14.360 --> 00:50:19.220 align:middle line:10%
to have the Monterey diocese
come and be at the Vatican

00:50:19.220 --> 00:50:23.420 align:middle line:10%
Pavilion as a best
practices example of how

00:50:23.420 --> 00:50:26.321 align:middle line:10%
to respond to the threat
of global climate change.

00:50:26.321 --> 00:50:28.070 align:middle line:84%
And we're going to be
doing that from June

00:50:28.070 --> 00:50:31.460 align:middle line:84%
to August at the big
pavilion to show people

00:50:31.460 --> 00:50:34.790 align:middle line:84%
how you participate concretely
in helping to bring down

00:50:34.790 --> 00:50:37.940 align:middle line:84%
global greenhouse gas emissions,
whether you're doing it

00:50:37.940 --> 00:50:41.150 align:middle line:84%
in response to Pope
Francis's papal encyclical,

00:50:41.150 --> 00:50:43.970 align:middle line:84%
or just because of the
response to the objective facts

00:50:43.970 --> 00:50:46.880 align:middle line:84%
and science that's
actually available for us.

00:50:46.880 --> 00:50:48.160 align:middle line:90%
That's what I would--

00:50:48.160 --> 00:50:50.840 align:middle line:84%
and so he has actually-- we
know what we'd like him to do.

00:50:50.840 --> 00:50:54.830 align:middle line:84%
He's invited us to come and be
a best example of how to respond

00:50:54.830 --> 00:50:56.584 align:middle line:90%
to the global climate change.

00:50:56.584 --> 00:50:58.250 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Well, you
seem to have your eye

00:50:58.250 --> 00:50:59.630 align:middle line:90%
on helping people, Daniel.

00:50:59.630 --> 00:51:02.000 align:middle line:84%
So continue doing
what you're doing.

00:51:02.000 --> 00:51:04.310 align:middle line:90%
Somebody's got to do it.

00:51:04.310 --> 00:51:07.280 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: All of us have
to do it, not just somebody.

00:51:07.280 --> 00:51:09.860 align:middle line:90%
Don't assign it to someone else.

00:51:09.860 --> 00:51:12.530 align:middle line:84%
Everybody needs to get on
board this thing right now

00:51:12.530 --> 00:51:15.650 align:middle line:84%
and do what every person
can do to try to draw down

00:51:15.650 --> 00:51:17.540 align:middle line:84%
these global greenhouse
gas emissions

00:51:17.540 --> 00:51:20.570 align:middle line:84%
and protect our
democratic institutions

00:51:20.570 --> 00:51:23.610 align:middle line:84%
from being taken over
by these oil, gas,

00:51:23.610 --> 00:51:25.130 align:middle line:90%
and coal corporations.

00:51:25.130 --> 00:51:27.591 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Thanks for being
on Beyond Belief, Daniel.

00:51:27.591 --> 00:51:29.840 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: It's a privilege
to get to be here, George.

00:51:29.840 --> 00:51:32.150 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Regardless
of how you believe

00:51:32.150 --> 00:51:34.580 align:middle line:84%
and what you think
about climate change,

00:51:34.580 --> 00:51:37.590 align:middle line:84%
there is no doubt
it's happening.

00:51:37.590 --> 00:51:39.320 align:middle line:90%
And it's happening fast.

00:51:39.320 --> 00:51:42.030 align:middle line:10%
And something has
to be done about it.

